{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17597772","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17597772"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:30:10+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:30:10+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15431"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15431","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15431"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.06,0.27,0.23,0.38]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8122"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63137"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8122","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8122"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15431"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48588"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4944"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7882"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"},{"type":"tags","id":"9511"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19693"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19697"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20614"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63137","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/63137"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EReactive arthritis is an inflammatory condition that is triggered by certain bacterial infections - and these are usually food-borne or sexually transmitted. The arthritis is separate from the infection and characteristically only appears once the bacterial infection has resolved. The reactive arthritis typically presents with joint pain and swelling, particularly affecting the lower limbs.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following organisms most commonly triggers reactive arthritis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Escherichia coli","Helicobacter pylori","Staphylococcus aureus","Streptococcus pyogenes","Chlamydia trachomatis"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChlamydia trachomatis\u003C/strong\u003E is one of the most common triggers of reactive arthritis, particularly following urogenital infection. The condition typically develops 2-3 weeks after the initial infection.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEscherichia coli\u003C/strong\u003E typically causes urinary tract infections but is not a common trigger of reactive arthritis. \u003Cstrong\u003EHelicobacter pylori\u003C/strong\u003E causes gastritis and peptic ulcer disease but is not associated with reactive arthritis. \u003Cstrong\u003EStaphylococcus aureus\u003C/strong\u003E typically causes septic arthritis rather than reactive arthritis. \u003Cstrong\u003EStreptococcus pyogenes\u003C/strong\u003E is associated with rheumatic fever but not reactive arthritis.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EOther organisms that commonly trigger reactive arthritis include Salmonella, Shigella, and Yersinia species following gastrointestinal infection.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Reactive arthritis commonly occurs 2-3 weeks after gastrointestinal or urogenital infections with specific organisms.","The classic triggering organisms for reactive arthritis can be remembered as CYST: Chlamydia, Yersinia, Salmonella, and Shigella."],"references":["Jubber A, Moorthy A. Reactive arthritis: a clinical review. J R Coll Physicians Edinb. 2021 Sep;51(3):288-297. doi: 10.4997/JRCPE.2021.319. PMID: 34528623.","Cheeti A, Chakraborty RK, Ramphul K. Reactive Arthritis. 2023 Jan 2. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29763006.","Kohnke SJ. Reactive arthritis. A clinical approach. Orthop Nurs. 2004 Jul-Aug;23(4):274-80. doi: 10.1097/00006416-200407000-00014. PMID: 15379179.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48588"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15431"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48588","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48588"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-20T09:23:58+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-20T09:24:28+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8122"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63137"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving